Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Company
    The Company class stores a list of Employees in an array and provides functions to add, remove, find, set hours and process payments.
    CompanyTest  
    Date
    A class that stores the date based off an input string.
    Employee
    Employee is a class that creates a new Employee object.
    FullTime
    A sub-class of the Employee class that shares the same information, such as profile and payment with the addition of salary that is unique to FullTime and its subclass.
    Management
    A sub-class of the FullTime class that shares the same information, such as profile, payment, and salary with the addition of role, representing 3 possible management positions.
    ManagementTest  
    PartTime
    A sub-class of the Employee that shares the same information, such as profile and payment with the addition of hourly and hoursWorked that is unique to PartTime.
    PayrollProcessing
    A class that drives the entire program and takes in all the command line arguments from the client
    Profile
    A class that stores the name, the department, and the date hired.All this information together forms an employee profile
    RunProject2
    Driver class for calling the run() method in PayrollProcessing to start the session for the client.
